              "text_aJpC6Q": {
                "type": "text",
                "name": "Text",
                "settings": {
                  "visibility": "always-display",
                  "text": "<p>Most dog owners laugh off \"dog breath\" as a quirky trait of being a pet parent. We hold our noses during morning cuddles or turn away when they try to lick our faces, assuming it's just part of the package. But that smell isn't just a nuisance—it’s the scent of active decay. Modern canine diets, filled with starches and sugars, have created a dental crisis that our pets are evolutionarily unprepared to handle, leaving their systemic health hanging by a thread.</p>",
