              "text_MaKbfY": {
                "type": "text",
                "settings": {
                  "visibility": "always-display",
                  "text": "<p>While we’ve been told for years to \"just give them a chew bone,\" the veterinary community is seeing a massive spike in chronic oral infections. For a dog, a mouth full of bacteria isn't just about losing teeth; it’s a direct highway to their internal organs. Because dogs are experts at masking pain, your pet could be suffering from throbbing gum inflammation for years before you notice a single symptom.</p><p>The struggle to maintain oral hygiene is real. Manual brushing is often a traumatic experience for both the pet and the owner, leading to a dangerous cycle of avoidance:</p>",
                  "alignment": "left",
                  "mobile_alignment": "mobile-center",
                  "text_size": 14,
